Class ClassroomsDailyTime

  • java.lang.Object
    • model.ClassroomsDailyTime
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, IClassroomsDailyTime

    public class ClassroomsDailyTime
extends java.lang.Object
implements IClassroomsDailyTime
    Implementation of the interface IClassroomsDailyTime through the usage of a Map that as a key shows the values of Classrooms.values() and to everyone it is associated a IDailyTime.

        public void add(ISubject sub,
                Classrooms room,
                int hour,
                int n)
        Description copied from interface: IClassroomsDailyTime
        It adds a subject in the daily timetable of a specific classroom. It must be possible for a teacher to have two different classrooms at the same time for the same subject, but it will be impossible for the same teacher to have two different subject at the same time in two different classrooms.
        Specified by:
        add in interface IClassroomsDailyTime
        Parameters:
        sub - Subject to be added.
        room - Classroom in which the lesson takes place.
        hour - Lesson starting time.
        n - Number of consecutive hour in which the subject passed as a parameter starting from hour is taught.
